The sentence "Flucht vor Moskau" can be translated to English as "Flight from Moscow." This could refer to a literal flight (such as an evacuation or escape) or a more figurative sense, depending on the context.
The fall of communism gave the nations of the former Soviet bloc the chance to turn toward democracy, the market economy, and the rule of law.
Some of these countries decisively broke off ties with their communist past; others were less successful, and a few have catastrophically failed.
